Additionally, the target must save vs. spells or be deafened for 5 rounds, resulting in a 50% chance of miscast magic. The target's Magic Resistance, if any, does not affect this spell.~
@6059   = ~Ruby Ray of Reversal~
@6060   = ~Ruby Ray of Reversal

Level: 7
Range: 40 ft.
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

When this spell is cast, it dispels one spell protection of any level affecting the target creature. The spells affected by Ruby Ray Of Reversal are Minor Spell Turning, Minor Globe of Invulnerability, Spell Immunity, Globe Of Invulnerability, Minor Spell Deflection, Spell Turning, Spell Shield, Spell Deflection, and Spell Trap. This will always remove the highest-level spell protection affecting the target; if more than one same-level protection is active on the target simultaneously, one of them will be randomly chosen and dispelled.

Additionally, if the target fails a save vs. spells, the target will be blinded by the Ruby Ray for 3 rounds. The target's Magic Resistance, if any, does not affect this spell.~
@6061   = ~Pierce Shield~
@6062   = ~Pierce Shield

Level: 8
Range: 40 ft.
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 8
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None 

When this spell is cast, it launches a massive attack on an enemy wizard's spell defenses. The target's Magic Resistance will be lowered by 10% + 1% per level of the caster. Next, Pierce Shield will cancel one spell protection of any level. The list of spells that this includes: Minor Spell Deflection, Minor Spell Turning, Spell Deflection, Minor Globe of Invulnerability, Spell Immunity, Globe Of Invulnerability, Spell Turning, Spell Shield, and Spell Trap. Finally, Pierce Shield will cancel the target's magical combat protections, such as Shield or Stoneskin (but specific protections, such as Resistance to Fire, will remain).

Magic Resistance does not affect this spell, nor do any of the spell protections. The resistance remains lowered for 1 round per level of the caster. It cannot be dispelled.~
@6063   = ~Minor Spell Absorption~
@6064   = ~Minor Spell Absorption

Level: 4
Range: 0
Duration: 1 turn
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: The caster
Saving Throw: None

This spell creates a barrier of magical protection around the spellcaster. Every spell that hits the barrier is absorbed, making the caster recall a previously cast spell. For example, if hit by a Flame Arrow (a 3rd-level spell), the caster will get three spell levels back—e.g. one spell of up to 3rd level in power. It excludes area effects that are not centered directly upon the wizard. As long as the spell is cast directly at the wizard, it will be reflected back upon the caster. This spell will only affect up to 4th-level spells, but as long as there are levels remaining, a spell will be absorbed. For example, if there is only 1 level left and a 3rd-level spell is cast at the wizard, the spell will be absorbed and will exhaust the protection.

This spell will absorb and protect against a total of 5 spell levels of magic directed at the caster. It will not protect the caster from Dispel Magic, but will not be dispelled by Dispel Magic either.~
@6065   = ~Spell Absorption~
@6066   = ~Spell Absorption

Level: 6
